import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import GlobalStyle from '../../src/Utils/GlobalStyle.js'
import InputText from '../../src/components/InputText/'

const layoutProps = {
  
};
export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}>
<GlobalStyle />
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"input"}}>{`Input`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`import Input from '../src/components/InputText/'`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<Playground __codesandbox={`undefined`} __position={1} __code={'<InputText id=\"user_name\" name=\"name\" label=\"Nick Name\" />\n<InputText id=\"user_email\" name=\"email\" label=\"Email\" />'} __scope={{props: this ? this.props : props,GlobalStyle,InputText}}>
    <InputText
        id='user_name'
        name='name'
        label='Nick Name'
    />
    <InputText
        id='user_email'
        name='email'
        label='Email'
    />
</Playground>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
